<p>Your <a href="/articles/thymosin-alpha-1-immune-guide">immune system</a> makes its own antibiotics. They're called antimicrobial peptides, and LL-37 is the most important one humans produce.</p>

<p>This 37-amino acid peptide does more than kill germs. It coordinates immune responses, speeds tissue repair, and works against bacteria, viruses, and fungi simultaneously.</p>

<div class="d">
